{"name": "gzip-stream", "metadata": {"name": "gzip-stream", "version": "1.2.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: CC0 1.0 Universal (CC0 1.0) Public Domain Dedication", "Operating System :: MacOS :: MacOS X", "Operating System :: POSIX", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries"], "home_page": "https://github.com/leenr/gzip-stream", "license": "", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Compress stream by GZIP on the fly.", "upload_time": 1638978439}, "documentation": ["# gzip-stream\n\n`gzip-stream` is a super-tiny library that will help you compress by GZIP\non-the-fly.\n\n`GZIPCompressedStream` class instance acting like an any other stream (in fact,\n`GZIPCompressedStream` inherits [io.RawIOBase](https://docs.python.org/3/library/io.html#io.RawIOBase)),\nbut wraps another stream and compress it on-the-fly.\n\n```python\nfrom gzip_stream import GZIPCompressedStream\nfrom my_upload_lib import MyUploadClient\n\nupload_client = MyUploadClient()\nwith open('my_very_big_1tb_file.txt') as file_to_upload:\n    compressed_stream = GZIPCompressedStream(\n        file_to_upload,\n        compression_level=7\n    )\n    upload_client.upload_fileobj(compressed_stream)\n```\n\n`GZIPCompressedStream` does not read entire stream, but instead read it\nby chunks, until compressed output size will not satisfy read size.\n\n`AsyncGZIPDecompressedStream` class can async read from another source\nwith zlib and gzip decompression on-the-fly\n\n```python\n# aiobotocore example\n\nimport aiobotocore\n\nfrom gzip_stream import AsyncGZIPDecompressedStream\n\nAWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID = \"KEY_ID\"\nAWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY = \"ACCESS_KEY\"\nBUCKET = \"AWESOME_BUCKET\"\n\nupload_client = MyAsyncUploadClient()\nsession = aiobotocore.get_session()\nasync with session.create_client(\n    service_name=\"s3\",\n    endpoint_url=\"s3_endpoint\",\n    aws_secret_access_key=AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY,\n    aws_access_key_id=AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID,\n) as client:\n    response = await client.get_object(Bucket=BUCKET, Key='my_very_big_1tb_file.txt.gz')\n    async for decompressed_chunk in GzipAsyncReaderWrapper(response[\"Body\"])):\n        await upload_client.upload_fileobj(decompressed_chunk)\n```\n\nModule works on Python ~= 3.5.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install gzip-stream\n```\n\n## License\n\nPublic Domain: [CC0 1.0 Universal](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/).\n"], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "gzip_stream", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "gzip_stream.BUFFER_SIZE", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "gzip_stream.GZIPCompressedStream", "bases": ["io.RawIOBase"], "methods": [{"name": "gzip_stream.GZIPCompressedStream.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "stream", "type": {"name": "BinaryIO", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.BinaryIO", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "compression_level", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gzip_stream.GZIPCompressedStream.compression_level", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gzip_stream.GZIPCompressedStream.stream", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "BinaryIO", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.BinaryIO", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gzip_stream.GZIPCompressedStream.readable", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gzip_stream.GZIPCompressedStream._read_compressed_into", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "b", "type": {"name": "memoryview", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.memoryview", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gzip_stream.GZIPCompressedStream.readinto", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "b", "type": {"name": "bytearray", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytearray", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gzip_stream.GZIPCompressedStream._read_n_compress", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "size", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "gzip_stream.GZIPCompressedStream.__repr__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": [